cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.DB 

This paper deals with embedding medical concepts in Electronic Medical Records (EMRs) using the attention mechanism to incorporate temporal information. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the categories of Natural Language Processing (NLP) and Machine Learning (ML) applied to healthcare data, which are covered by cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves information retrieval (IR) and artificial intelligence (AI) techniques to cluster and search for nearest neighbors of medical codes, which are relevant to cs.IR and cs.AI. Finally, the paper deals with EMRs, which are a type of database, and therefore, it could be relevant to cs.DB (Databases).
